PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Possible Ransomware File Rename Activity Over Network Share
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This is a heuristic based rule to detect too many SMB rename operations over the network. The rule will detect the number of SMB file rename operations during the defined number of seconds. After the malicious source is detected the rule will prevent any further SMB file rename and write operation from that source for the defined period of time.
Configuration Note: The rule also has configuration option to exclude the IPs of the client machines doing rename operations.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Possible Ransomware File Rename Activity Over Network Share - Client
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This is a heuristic based rule to detect too many SMB rename operations over the network.The rule will detect the number of SMB file rename operations during the defined number of seconds. After the malicious source is detected the rule will prevent any further SMB file rename and write operation on SMB shares for the defined period of time.
Configuration Note: The rule also has configuration option to exclude the IPs of the SMB Shares where renames operation can be performed by client machine.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Reflected File Download Attack
PayloadFilter2.Description:
Reflected File Download (RFD) is a web attack vector that enables attackers to gain complete control over a user system. In an RFD attack, the user follows a malicious link to a trusted domain resulting in a file download from that domain.
Note: Configuration option is provided to add the executable file extensions to block the RFD attack for the file extensions. Administrators are suggested to add executable file extensions to block the RFD attack according to their Web Application file extension support. The triggers of this rule have to be investigated further to confirm their domain are being used to carry out RFD attack.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Microsoft Graphics Component Remote Code Execution Vulnerability (CVE-2013-3906) - 5
PayloadFilter2.Description: A remote code execution vulnerability that exists in the way affected components handle specially crafted TIFF images. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability by convincing a user to open a specially crafted file, or browse specially crafted web content.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified WebNMS Framework Server Sensitive File Access (ATT&CK T1552.001)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects an attempt to access a sensitive installation file in WebNMS Framework Server. While not inherently malicious, known vulnerabilities exist in which an unauthorised entity could access sensitive installation information in WebNMS Framework Server. An attacker could leverage this to obtain passwords for all user accounts.
Configuration Note: Configuration options are provided to set the IP(s) of trusted host(s) to pass traffic.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Disallow Upload Of A PHP File (ATT&CK T1190)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This is a heuristic based rule to identify the upload of PHP files to a Web Server. These files could be potentially harmful for running applications and could be used for further attacks.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious China Chopper Webshell Communication (ATT&CK T1505.003)
PayloadFilter2.Description: China Chopper Webshell is a malware designed to remotely access Windows or Linux Web servers. The malware has a Web shell command-and-control (CnC) client binary and a text-based Web shell payload (server component). Post infection, the malware enables remote attackers to execute arbitrary code on affected systems. This is a heuristic based rule which detects the HTTP communication of China chopper Webshell.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Web Server Restrict Executable File Uploads (ATT&CK T1190)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This filter blocks EXE file uploads. Administrator can configure this filter and allow certain EXE file uploads.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Too Many SSL Alert Messages In SSLv3 Over RDP (ATT&CK T1021.001, T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This is a heuristic based rule to detect too many SSL alert messages from a server within a period of time. Such large number of alert messages could be an indication of block-wise chosen-boundary attack, which could allow an attacker to obtain plain-text bytes using SSLv3 protocol.
Configuration Note: Configuration options are provided to customize the alert frequency of the events. Multiple alert messages in SSLv3 protocol can occur legitimately due to server limitations. Hence, every trigger of this rule should be investigated further to confirm an attack.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Microsoft SharePoint GetGroupInfo Request (ATT&CK T1213.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects a UserGroup.GetGroupInfo request to a Microsoft SharePoint instance. The UserGroup.GetGroupInfo method returns information on a specified group from a SharePoint Web site.
Note: This rule might generate a lot of triggers when applied on a Microsoft SharePoint Server.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Detect UPX Packed Executable Download (ATT&CK T1027.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description: UPX is a universal file compressor and packer for executable files. This filter blocks the download to UPX packed executable files.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Microsoft SharePoint GetGroupCollectionFromRole Request (ATT&CK T1213.002, T1087)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects a UserGroup.GetGroupCollectionFromRole request to a Microsoft SharePoint instance. The UserGroup.GetGroupCollectionFromRole method returns group information for a SharePoint Web site collection.
Note: This DPI rule might generate a lot of triggers when applied on a Microsoft SharePoint Server.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Microsoft SharePoint GetGroupCollection Request (ATT&CK T1213.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects a UserGroup.GetGroupCollection request to a Microsoft SharePoint instance. The UserGroup.GetGroupCollection method returns information on a specified group from a SharePoint Web site.
Note: This DPI rule might generate a lot of triggers when applied on a Microsoft SharePoint Server.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Microsoft SharePoint GetGroupCollectionFromUser Request (ATT&CK T1213.002, T1087)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects a UserGroup.GetGroupCollectionFromUser request to a Microsoft SharePoint instance. The UserGroup.GetGroupCollectionFromUser method returns information on the collection of groups of which a specified user is a member from a SharePoint Web site.
Note: This DPI rule might generate a lot of triggers when applied on a Microsoft SharePoint Server.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Potentially Malicious RAT Traffic - VII (ATT&CK T1571)
PayloadFilter2.Description: A remote access tool (or RAT) is a software used to access a remote computer often used for malicious activities. This smart rule identifies suspicious RAT traffic.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Microsoft SharePoint GetRoleCollection Request (ATT&CK T1213.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects a UserGroup.GetRoleCollection request to a Microsoft SharePoint instance. The UserGroup.GetRoleCollection method returns information about the role definitions from a SharePoint Web site.
Note: This DPI Rule might generate a lot of triggers when applied on a Microsoft SharePoint Server.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Potentially Malicious RAT Traffic - I (ATT&CK T1571)
PayloadFilter2.Description: A remote access tool (or RAT) is a software used to access a remote computer often used for malicious activities. This smart rule identifies suspicious RAT traffic.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Microsoft SharePoint GetGroupCollectionFromWeb Request (ATT&CK T1213.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects a UserGroup.GetGroupCollectionFromWeb request to a Microsoft SharePoint instance. The UserGroup.GetGroupCollectionFromWeb method returns information on the collection of groups from a SharePoint Web site.
Note: This DPI rule might generate a lot of triggers when applied on a Microsoft SharePoint Server.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Microsoft SharePoint GetGroupCollectionFromSite Request (ATT&CK T1213.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects a UserGroup.GetGroupCollectionFromSite request to a Microsoft SharePoint instance. The UserGroup.GetGroupCollectionFromSite method returns information on the collection of groups from a SharePoint Web site.
Note: This DPI rule might generate a lot of triggers when applied on a Microsoft SharePoint Server.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified HTTP Backdoor.Win32.Cobalt.SMHP C&C Traffic Request
PayloadFilter2.Description: This alert is triggered when traffic matching a known Command and Control pattern is observed. Events from this filter are typically indicative of network activity from a breached host.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Potentially Malicious RAT Traffic - V (ATT&CK T1571)
PayloadFilter2.Description: A remote access tool (or RAT) is a software used to access a remote computer often used for malicious activities. This smart rule identifies suspicious RAT traffic.

PayloadFilter2.Name: SMB DLL Injection Exploit Detected (ATT&CK T1055.001)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This rule is based on heuristics and will detect dll injection attack is being performed using SMB share. This rule could generate many alerts on some network environment hence each trigger needs further investigation to ensure attack.
Note: This rule only detects traffic and does not block.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Microsoft SharePoint Server Remote Code Execution Vulnerability (CVE-2021-42309)
PayloadFilter2.Description: A remote code execution exists in affected installations of Microsoft SharePoint. Authentication is required to exploit this vulnerability. The specific flaw exists within the handling of server-side controls. An unsafe server-side control can be instantiated if it is specified as a child of a permitted control. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to execute code in the context of the service account.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Zoho ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus Stored Cross-Site Scripting Vulnerability (CVE-2021-46065)
PayloadFilter2.Description: Zoho ManageEngine ServiceDesk Plus is vulnerable to stored cross-site scripting. A remote, authenticated attacker can exploit this vulnerability by sending a crafted request to the server. Successful exploitation could result in the execution of script code in security context of the target user's browser.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Microsoft SharePoint GetPermissionCollection Request (ATT&CK T1069, T1213.002, T1589.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects a Permissions.GetPermissionCollection request to Microsoft SharePoint. The Permissions.GetPermissionCollection method returns the collection of permissions for a SharePoint site or list.
Note: This rule might generate a lot of triggers when applied on a Microsoft SharePoint Server.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Zoho ManageEngine ADManager Plus Unrestricted File Upload Vulnerability (CVE-2021-37926)
PayloadFilter2.Description: Zoho ManageEngine ADManager Plus is prone to an unrestricted file upload vulnerability. A remote authenticated attacker can exploit the vulnerability by sending crafted requests to the server. Successful exploitation could result in unrestricted file upload and remote code execution in the security context as SYSTEM.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Telegram Bot API Usage (Used by Telecrypt) (ATT&CK T1102.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This filter detects an attempt to use the Telegram API. Telegram is an instant messaging application. The service provides an interface to create custom communication bots.
NOTE: Telegram Bot service has been known to be used by malware like Telecrypt for communication.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Detected Vkontakte Site Access Over HTTP (ATT&CK T1102.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description: Adversaries may use an existing, legitimate external Web service as a means for relaying commands to a compromised system. This filter detects an attempt to access the Vkontakte website.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified HTTP Request Smuggling Attack
PayloadFilter2.Description:
HTTP Request Smuggling consists of sending a specially formatted HTTP request that will be parsed in a different way by the proxy system and by the final system, so the attacker could smuggle a request to one system without the other being aware of it. This may lead to bypassing Web Application Firewall protection/Web Proxy and improper cache at Web Cache Servers. Please refer the Details section for more information.
Note: This DPI rule should be preferably applied at in-line proxies. Configuration options are provided to block different attack vectors of HTTP Request Smuggling.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified SambaShell C&C Traffic
PayloadFilter2.Description: This DPI rule is intended to block known malicious C&C traffic.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious Command Injection Attack - 1
PayloadFilter2.Description: Command injection is an attack technique that allows an attacker to inject and execute commands in the vulnerable application. An attacker can exploit command injection vulnerability with a command sequence appended to the appropriate format or escape string to execute arbitrary commands. Successful exploitation results in a system compromise, disclosure or modification of data. This is a heuristic based rule to block command injection attacks. In some network environment further investigation will be required to confirm the attack.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious User Agent In Outgoing HTTP Request
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This is a heuristic based rule which identifies the suspicious user-agent header in outgoing HTTP request used for connecting to command and control server.
Note: Configuration options are provided to configure additional user agents and the alert frequency of the events.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Slow HTTP Denial Of Service Attack (ATT&CK T1498.001)
PayloadFilter2.Description: Adversaries may attempt to cause a denial of service (DoS) by directly sending a high-volume of network traffic to a target

PayloadFilter2.Name: Restrict Microsoft .Net Executable File Upload (ATT&CK T1190)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This is a generic rule to prevent any upload of Microsoft .Net executable over HTTP. Attackers may use malicious Microsoft .NET executable files to cause remote code execution.
Note: This DPI rule should be applied ONLY in server environments where upload of Microsoft .Net executable over HTTP is not allowed.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Zoho ManageEngine OpManager SumPDU Multiple Java Deserialization Vulnerabilities (CVE-2020-28653 and CVE-2021-3287)
PayloadFilter2.Description: An HTTP endpoint used by the Manage Engine OpManager Smart Update Manager component can be leveraged to deserialize an arbitrary Java object. This can be abused by an unauthenticated remote attacker to execute OS commands in the context of the OpManager application. This vulnerability is also present in other products that are built on top of the OpManager application.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Microsoft Windows OLE Remote Code Execution Vulnerability - 1
PayloadFilter2.Description: A vulnerability exists in Windows OLE that could allow remote code execution if a user opens a file that contains a specially crafted OLE object. An attacker who successfully exploited this vulnerability could gain the same user rights as the logged-on user.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious Upload Of Archive File (ATT&CK T1190)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This is a heuristic based rule to block the upload of certain archive files. The uploaded file could contain malicious code in the form of an exploit, virus, Trojan or malware, which could be used to gain control of the Web server.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Disallow Upload Of A JSP File (ATT&CK T1190)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This is a heuristic based rule to identify the upload of JSP files to a Web Server. These files could be potentially harmful for running applications and could be used for further attacks.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious Obfuscated JavaScript - 3 (ATT&CK T1203, T1001)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This DPI rule detects suspicious obfuscated JavaScript used by attackers to bypass security and gain unauthorized access to the system. Legitimate web sites could also obfuscate code to reduce security exposure or for intellectual property protection.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious Obfuscated JavaScript - 4 (ATT&CK T1203, T1001)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This DPI rule detects suspicious obfuscated JavaScript used by attackers to bypass security and gain unauthorized access to the system.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Detected Too Many Suspicious TLS/SSL Client Hello Messages (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This is a heuristic rule intended to detect too many TLS/SSL Client Hello messages containing a Session Ticket extension with a non-zero Extension Length. With a large number of invalid session tickets, a remote attacker can cause a denial of service.
Note: Configuration options are provided to update the frequency of Client Hello messages.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Web Application Possible Brute Force Attempt (ATT&CK T1110)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This rule blocks brute force attempt to web application by inspecting the number of error responses in a given time period. The IP address is blocked for 20 minutes after the brute force attempt is detected.
Note: Configuration option should be used to enter custom error response.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious Obfuscated JavaScript (ATT&CK T1203, T1001)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects suspicious obfuscated JavaScript used by attackers to bypass security and gain unauthorized access to the system. Legitimate web sites could also obfuscate code to reduce security exposure or for intellectual property protection.
Note: The triggers of this rule have to be investigated further to confirm attacks.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified TLS/SSL RC4 Cipher Suite Is Being Supported (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
The RC4 algorithm, as used in the TLS protocol and SSL protocol, has many single-byte biases, which makes it easier for remote attackers to conduct plaintext-recovery attacks via statistical analysis of ciphertext in a large number of sessions that use the same plaintext.
Note: This is a heuristic based rule which identifies the RC4 algorithm being used in SSL/TLS traffic.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Weak Cipher Support From TLS/SSL Server (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description: TLS/SSL server supporting cipher suites based on weak algorithms may enable an attacker to launch man-in-the-middle attacks and monitor or tamper with sensitive data. In general, these ciphers are considered weak. This is a heuristic based rule, which logs SSL traffic with weak Cipher.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Restrict OpenSSL TLS/DTLS Heartbeat Message (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
OpenSSL contains a flaw in its implementation of the TLS/DTLS (Transport layer security protocols) heartbeat functionality which allows an attacker to retrieve sensitive information. This DPI rule is intended to prevent TLS/DTLS heartbeat message coming from a SSL Server.
Note: Configuration options are provided to customize the alert frequency of the events.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Compression Algorithm In SSL/TLS Message (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects the usage of compression algorithm in SSL/TLS traffic. The TLS protocol can encrypt compressed data without properly obfuscating the length of the unencrypted data, which allows man-in-the-middle attackers to obtain plaintext HTTP headers by observing length differences during a series of guesses in which a string in an HTTP request potentially matches an unknown string in an HTTP header, aka a "CRIME" attack.
Note: Compression algorithm in SSL/TLS protocol is also used for legitimate purpose due to server limitations. Hence, every trigger of this rule should be investigated further to confirm an attack. Configuration options are provided to customize the alert frequency of the events.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious Obfuscated JavaScript - 1 (ATT&CK T1203, T1001)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects suspicious obfuscated JavaScript used by attackers to bypass security and gain unauthorized access to the system. Legitimate web sites could also obfuscate code to reduce security exposure or for intellectual property protection.
Note: The triggers of this rule have to be investigated further to confirm attacks.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified TLS/SSL DES Cipher Suite Is Being Supported (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
A cipher block collision vulnerability has been reported in the OpenSSL 3 Data Encryption Standard (3DES) and Data Encryption Standard (DES) ciphers. The vulnerability is due to use of small block size (64-bit) in 3DES. A remote attacker can exploit this vulnerability by monitoring the traffic over long session. Successful exploitation may result in the plaintext recovery of the monitored encrypted traffic.
Note: This is a heuristic based rule which identifies the DES algorithm being used in SSL/TLS traffic.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified OpenSSL DTLS Anonymous ECDH Cipher Suite (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This DPI rule detects the usage of anonymous ECDH ciphersuite in DTLS traffic. OpenSSL DTLS clients enabling anonymous ECDH ciphersuites are subject to a denial of service attack. A malicious server can crash the client with a null pointer dereference (read) by specifying an anonymous ECDH ciphersuite and sending carefully crafted handshake messages.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious Usage Of Shellcode For Client
PayloadFilter2.Description: Shellcode is a piece of machine code used as the payload in the exploitation of a software vulnerability. This filter will identify common shellcode exploits and some zero day attacks in web client traffic

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Too Many Compressed HTTP Responses (ATT&CK T1071.001)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
Data compression algorithms can be used by web servers to compress the HTTP responses. BREACH security tool exploits a property of compression algorithms to steal sensitive data. This is a heuristic based rule to identify too many compressed HTTP responses within a period of time.
Note: Configuration options are provided to set the count, time period and event frequency of this rule. To monitor SSL Data Stream, agent (DSA) needs to be configured via "SSL Configuration Wizard" and has to acquire the Server SSL certificate where DPI rule is assigned.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified CBC Based Cipher Suite In SSLv3 Request (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects the usage of CBC Based cipher suites in SSLv3.0 traffic. The CBC Based cipher suites use symmetric encryption algorithm in vulnerable SSL/TLS protocols to encrypt data with chained initialization vectors, which allows man-in-the-middle attackers to obtain plain-text HTTP headers via a block-wise chosen-boundary attack on an HTTPS session.
Configuration Note: CBC Based cipher suites in SSLv3.0 protocol are also used for legitimate purpose due to server limitations. Hence, every trigger of this rule should be investigated further to confirm an attack. A configuration option is provided to set the event frequency and to create an approved list of IP addresses that are allowed to communicate using CBC based cipher suite over SSLv3. The filter detects traffic in the default configuration.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Detected SSLv3 Response (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This is a heuristic rule intended to detect SSL version 3.0 Response.
Configuration Note: A configuration option is provided to set the event frequency and to create an approved list of IP addresses that are allowed to communicate over SSLv3. The filter detects traffic in the default configuration.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Download Of DLL File Over WebDAV (ATT&CK T1574.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This rule is based on heuristics and will detect/prevent DLL file being requested to WebDAV server.
Note: This rule should be applied when DLL files are not expected to be downloaded from the WebDAV shares.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious Obfuscated PDF Document (ATT&CK T1027, T1204.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule is intended to block suspicious PDF documents which are obfuscated using lexical conventions.
Note: This rule is always recommended when any version of PDF reader is installed on the computer.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious RTF File With Obfuscated PowerShell Execution (ATT&CK T1027, T1204.002, T1059.001)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This is a heuristic based rule intended to block attempts to load suspicious Microsoft Word RTF files containing PowerShell code, over HTTP traffic.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Usage Of EXPORT Cipher Suite In SSLv2 Connection (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
Export Cipher suites, as used in the SSLv2 protocol, are very weak and it is easy for remote attackers to conduct plain text-recovery attacks.
Note: This is a heuristic based rule which identifies if any Export cipher suites are being used in SSLv2 connection.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Revoked Certificate Authority In SSL Traffic (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This rule prevents the use of revoked/unauthorized Root/Intermediate CAs based on the list of configured CA/Issuers.
Note: Configuration options are provided to configure CA (Certificate Authority).

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified SSL/TLS Diffie-Hellman Key Exchange Using Weak Parameters Client (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This rule is intended to identify Diffie-Hellman Ephemeral Cipher suites using parameters with 512 bits length. The SSL/TLS session keys created with weak parameters could allow an attacker to recover the plain text on the encrypted channel.
This rule will detect if the SSL/TLS client is using DHE weak parameters.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Usage Of TLS/SSL EXPORT Cipher Suite In Request (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
Export Cipher suites, as used in the TLS protocol and SSL protocol, are very weak and it is easy for remote attackers to conduct plaintext-recovery attacks.
Note: This is a heuristic based rule which identifies if any Export cipher suite being used in SSL/TLS traffic.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified OpenSSL SRP Cipher Suite In Server Hello Message (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This DPI rule detects the usage of SRP cipher suite in server hello message. OpenSSL clients enabling SRP ciphersuites are subject to a denial of service attack. A malicious server can crash the client with a null pointer dereference (read) by specifying an SRP ciphersuite even though it was not properly negotiated with the client.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Compression Algorithm In SSL/TLS (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule detects the usage of compression algorithm in SSL/TLS traffic. The TLS protocol can encrypt compressed data without properly obfuscating the length of the unencrypted data, which allows man-in-the-middle attackers to obtain plaintext HTTP headers by observing length differences during a series of guesses in which a string in an HTTP request potentially matches an unknown string in an HTTP header, aka a "CRIME" attack.
Note: Compression algorithm in SSL/TLS protocol is also used for legitimate purpose due to server limitations. Hence, every trigger of this rule should be investigated further to confirm an attack. Configuration options are provided to customize the alert frequency of the events.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious OpenSSL TLS/DTLS Heartbeat Request (ATT&CK T1573.002)
PayloadFilter2.Description: The TLS and DTLS implementations in OpenSSL do not properly handle Heartbeat Extension packets, which allow remote attackers to obtain sensitive information from process memory via crafted packets. This is a heuristic based rule to identify such suspicious Heartbeat requests.

PayloadFilter2.Name: FTP Server Restrict Executable File Uploads (ATT&CK T1105)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This DPI rule blocks EXE file uploads. Administrator can configure this rule and allow certain EXE file uploads.
NOTE: This DPI rule only checks the data transfer in PASV mode.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Apache APISIX Remote Code Execution Vulnerability (CVE-2020-13945)
PayloadFilter2.Description: Apache APISIX is vulnerable to remote code execution vulnerability. The vulnerability is due to using a default built-in admin API access token which may lead to unauthenticated remote command execution.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious Image Files Over HTTP
PayloadFilter2.Description: This DPI rule detects malicious BMP and GIF files. Such files can exploit a weakness in image parsing libraries to execute attack on victim's browser.

PayloadFilter2.Name: POP3 Mail Server Possible Brute Force Attempt (ATT&CK T1110)
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This rule blocks brute force attempt to POP3 mail server by inspecting the number of invalid login attempts in a given time period. The IP address is blocked for 20 minutes after the brute force attempt is detected.
Note: Configuration option can be used to enter error responses of the mail server to be monitored.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Disallow Upload Of A Class File (ATT&CK T1190)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This is a heuristic based rule to identify the upload of Class files to a Web Server. These files could be potentially harmful for running applications and could be used for further attacks.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified SSL/TLS Diffie-Hellman Key Exchange Using Weak Parameters Server (ATT&CK T1573.002)

PayloadFilter2.Description:

PayloadFilter2.Description: This filter detects a brute force attempt to gain the FTP Server Password by inspecting the number of failed logins in a time period. An attacker may use automated tools to iterate through all combinations or use a dictionary attack to guess passwords.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Telnet Server Possible Brute Force Attempt (ATT&CK T1110)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This filter detects a brute force attempt to gain the Telnet Server Password by inspecting the number of failed logins in a time period. An attacker may use automated tools to iterate through all combinations or use a dictionary attack to guess passwords.

PayloadFilter2.Description: Remote Procedure Call (RPC) is an interprocess communication (IPC) mechanism that enables data exchange and invocation of functionality residing in a different process. A client will call the endpoint mapper (EPM) at the server to ask for a "well known" service. The server will answer the client at which port this service is available. This rule decodes the port shared by the Server using DCE/RPC Endpoint Mapper (EPM) Protocol, and help other rules for monitoring traffic on the dynamically opened port.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Windows DCERPC AUTH LEVEL CONNECT Password Validate Request

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Suspicious Bash ShellShock Attack
PayloadFilter2.Description:
Bash is prone to a remote code execution vulnerability when it incorrectly processes trailing strings after certain malformed function definitions in the values of environment variables, which allows remote attackers to write to files or possibly have unknown other impact via a crafted request. This is a heuristic based rule to detect such attacks.
Note: In some network environment this rule could generate many alerts, hence every trigger should be investigated further to confirm the attack.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Microsoft Teams amsVideo Cross Site Scripting Vulnerability (ZDI-CAN-13482)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This vulnerability allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code on affected installations of Microsoft Teams Desktop. The specific flaw exists within the handling of the amsVideo parameter provided to the Teams endpoint. The issue results from the lack of proper validation of user-supplied data, which can lead to the injection of an arbitrary script. An attacker can leverage this in conjunction with other vulnerabilities to execute arbitrary code in the context of the current process.

Successful exploitation would allow an attacker to read arbitrary files on the system, potentially disclosing sensitive information.

A remote attacker can exploit this vulnerability by enticing a target user into clicking a malicious link. Successful exploitation could result in arbitrary script execution in the target user's browser.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Microsoft SharePoint Server Remote Code Execution Vulnerability (CVE-2021-40487)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This vulnerability allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code on affected installations of Microsoft SharePoint. Authentication is required to exploit this vulnerability. The specific flaw exists within the Microsoft.SharePoint.WorkflowActions.SetVariableActivity class. A crafted SetVariableActivity element can result in instantiation of an arbitrary .NET type. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to execute code in the context of the web service account.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Microsoft Project MPT File Parsing Out-Of-Bounds Read Vulnerability (ZDI-CAN-14518)
PayloadFilter2.Description: This vulnerability allows remote attackers to disclose sensitive information on affected installations of Microsoft Project. The specific flaw exists within the parsing of MPT files. The issue results from the lack of proper validation of user-supplied data, which can result in a read past the end of an allocated buffer. An attacker can leverage this vulnerability to disclose information in the context of the current process.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Detected Wget Client Traffic
PayloadFilter2.Description:
This is a heuristics based filter to detect HTTP Client traffic by using Wget user agent. For mission critical servers, limited HTTP client traffic means those servers will have less exposure to web related attacks. It also prevents potential backdoor software from contacting external malicious sites.
This filter will be triggered once per minute for a given host. The frequency of event settings can be modified on the Configuration tab should your environment require different configuration.

PayloadFilter2.Name: HTTP Protocol Decoding
PayloadFilter2.Description: Required by all other HTTP DPI rules. This DPI rule decodes the HTTP protocol, restricts URI and query lengths, and validates URI encoding.

PayloadFilter2.Name: Identified Attempt To Brute Force Windows Login Credentials (ATT&CK T1110)

Configuration Note: Customers are advised to use the configuration options to tune the rule as per their environment.
